item.title: Hayden Panettiere Pays Tribute To Brother Jansen In First TV Interview Since His Tragic Death
item.description: NHayden Panettiere paid tribute to her brother Jansen on Mondays “Good Morning America” in her first TV interview since his tragic death. Jansen died on Feb. 19 of an enlarged heart at age just 28.
item.author: joelxdnq@gmail.com (joel)

item.title: STEVE Harvey has been left "scared" of a Family Feud contestant after their intense face-off response on stage..
item.description: The gameshow's network shared the clip of the interaction on the Family Feud Instagram account.During one of the episode's contestant face-offs, Steve, 66, asked: "Tell me something that's known as a bloodsucker?" Laura, one of the two players competing for their teams immediately smashed the buzzer and growled out: "A man!" The comedian appeared to be disturbed by the answer as he stood motionless with a pleading, "help me" expression on his face. The studio audience could be heard laughing at Laura's response and the game show host's fearful reaction to it.
item.author: joelxdnq@gmail.com (joel)

item.title: Former child star Frankie Muniz now a professional racing driver
item.description: TFrankie Muniz is finally getting to live his dream. The child star was a staple on screens throughout the early 2000s, starring as the lead in the TV series Malcolm in the Middle and the Agent Cody Banks movies among other roles. Now 37 years old, Muniz’s career is set to take a swift detour after he announced that he will be competing in NASCAR’s ARCA Menards Series championship this year, The Sun reports.
item.author: joelxdnq@gmail.com (joel)
